Well, Rangers/monks/rogues speak for themselves.<br>
<br>
Knights with top end velious 2h can match and exceed warrior damage.   With top end Luclin ones they can usually do more. Certainly more if the warrior is dual weilding, ESPECIALLY against luclin super-ac mobs.  Without defensive (which lasts 3/10 of an ubermob fight at takes away 40% of the warrior's offence) a knight is every bit as good a tank as the warrior.  <br>
<br>
If warriors aren't going to be the very best tanks, and have no spells, and be on the lower half of the meele damage (the diff between knights and warriors isn't much... but for the spells and AA skills hybrids get they have it much better).<br>
<br>
Warriors as-is now are good for one thing... MT for an ubermob.  In any other capacity they are a handicap.   The shield idea isn't bad if it comes with balance.. but the warriors really really need a bone if they are gonna lose their tanking superiority  after watching every other meele class get so many boosts in the last year while we got nothing.   Oh, we got AE taunt (which isn't all bad) and our epics (which can be replaced 10x easier than it is to get them in the first place) can be used either hand.  Wheee.<br>
<br>
It's all defensive's fault too.... without that we could be made the best overall pure meeles hands down and still be balanced for lack of spells/skills.  Balancing with defensive in mind is tricky.   <p>Gurunt Bangoo <Wraith>
